item.title: Associative
item.description: In math, associative refers to the property where the way numbers are grouped (using parentheses) in an operation does not affect the final result, as long as the order of the numbers remain unchanged. Xor is Associative.

item.title: assembly
item.description: ~When writing programs in assembly code, a coder must specify the low-level instructions the program uses to carry out a computation Assembly code is highly machine specific
